ornia/imperial/el centro/"], "contributor": ["university of california, riverside; riverside, ca"], "date": "1930-12-11", "dates": ["1930-12-11"], "description": ["6 REQUESTS FOR GAME TICKETS PROVING HEAVY PASADENA Dec 11 Special Ticket applications for the Alaba maWashington State Rose Bowl football game have been remark ably heavy during the first week Earl V Foster general director an nounced Blanks were mailed to 45 000 persons on the conference mailing lists while chambers of commerce in 70 Southern Califor nia communities also distributed the ticket forms All ticket applications should be returned to the general headquar ters Pacific Southwest Building Pasadena before December 15 Af ter that day the tickets will be placed on general sale and mail applications will be filled out ot the remaining tickets The policy of first come first served adopted by the game man agement in the sale of tickets has brought immediate response from those wishing choice scats Because of the small following of alumni of the respective rival teams the public is enjoying the privilege of buying the best seats in the bowl For several years the center sec tions have been taken by the alum ni groups of the participating schools The Palo Verde Valley has 240 acres of pecans some of them four years old and bearing good crops for young trees"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-09-02T13:59:03.180Z", "group": ["ndnp/curiv", "university-of-california-riverside-riverside-ca-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92070146/1930-12-11/ed-1/?sp=12", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:curiv:batch_curiv_paperflower_ver01:data:sn92070146:0041418859A:1930121101:1082/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=463&w=366", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:curiv:batch_curiv_paperflower_ver01:data:sn92070146:0041418859A:1930121101:1082/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=926&w=733", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coo